Author: Mallela Sathya Prajith Reddy <sathyaprajith5929@gmail.com>
Commit: Mallela Sathya Prajith Reddy <sathyaprajith5929@gmail.com>

    Migrate to Ollama, fix WhatsApp logout/summary flow, remove Meets, gate Discord on token
    
    AI engine:
    - Replace Google Gemini with Ollama (minimax-m3:cloud on localhost:11434) via a
      new shared backend/llm.js exposing a Gemini-compatible interface (text +
      native vision; multi-host round-robin + failover; transient-error retries).
    - RAG server uses Ollama embeddings with a no-DB file-backed vector store
      fallback (server/vectorStore.js); Postgres still used when DATABASE_URL is set.
    
    WhatsApp:
    - Fix lost-summary-on-navigate bug: analyses now register in a route-stable job
      store (startJob), and "is analyzing" derives reactively from it so the spinner
      survives navigation and auto-clears on completion.
    - Fix slow logout->new-QR: /api/logout responds immediately and tears down in the
      background; auth folder is renamed (instant) + deleted in the background instead
      of blocking; no 30s post-scan reconnect delay; SIGINT no longer wipes the session.
    - Surface AI-summary failures with a retry card; clearer connection/offline states.
    
    Discord:
    - Optional bot token: backend boots without one and exposes POST /api/connect; the
      UI shows a token-setup screen instead of an infinite spinner.
    
    UI:
    - Remove the Three.js WebGL shader background (and the three dep) for a lightweight
      CSS gradient; readable Inter body font with the pixel font reserved for headings;
      fix mojibake; general polish.
    
    Cleanup:
    - Remove the Meets feature entirely (backend, page, routes, data, docs, CSS).
    - Prune unused deps; update README/.env.example/docs; ignore runtime artifacts.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
